  planner_response {
    modified_response: "I\'ve implemented a robust fix for the \"selection jumping\" and \"whole page selection\" issues.\n\n### Key Fixes:\n1.  **Selection Stability (CSS)**:\n    *   Changed the `textLayer` container to `user-select: text` but kept it `pointer-events: none`. This allows the browser\'s selection engine to smoothly maintain its state when dragging across gaps between words or lines without \"panicking\" and jumping to find the next selectable block.\n    *   Ensured selection can only *start* on actual text spans by keeping them `pointer-events: auto`.\n    *   Set spans to `display: block` to provide more predictable vertical boundaries for the selection engine.\n\n2.  **Accuracy & Jump Prevention (Logic)**:\n    *   Updated the selection loop in `PDFReader.tsx` to use high-precision `range.getClientRects()`.\n    *   Added a **Selection Guard**: Before processing, the system now checks if the selection\'s start or end points are actually inside the text layer. If the browser tries to \"jump\" the selection to an area outside the current page (a common glitch when dragging into dead space), the highlight is suppressed.\n    *   Implemented tighter intersection logic to ensure only the portion of the selection actually visible on the current page is highlighted.\n\nThese changes combined should stop the selection from expanding to the whole page and make it strictly follow your finger or mouse cursor without \"guessing\" or snapping unpredictably.\n\n"
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
steps {
