  user_input {
    user_response: ":::writing{variant=\342\200\234chat_message\342\200\235 id=\342\200\23435821\342\200\235}\nInvestigate mobile text selection overflow bug in the PDF reader.\n\nCurrent issue:\nWhen selecting text and dragging selection handles near the end of a word/line, the browser suddenly falls back to selecting the entire page/container instead of continuing precise text selection.\n\nThis mainly happens:\n\t\342\200\242\tnear line edges\n\t\342\200\242\tnear page top\n\t\342\200\242\twhen extending Arabic text selection\n\t\342\200\242\twhen selection leaves valid text spans momentarily\n\nLikely cause:\nThe browser is losing valid selectable text targets and falling back to the nearest selectable ancestor/container.\n\nRequired fixes:\n\t1.\tPrevent ALL parent/container selection fallback.\nApply:\n\n.page,\n.page-wrapper,\n.reader-sheet,\n.spread-page,\n.transform-container {\n  user-select: none !important;\n  -webkit-user-select: none !important;\n}\n\nOnly .textLayer and .textLayer span should remain selectable.\n\t2.\tStrengthen text span hit areas.\nApply:\n\n.textLayer span {\n  display: inline-block;\n  min-height: 1em;\n  padding-top: 1px;\n  padding-bottom: 1px;\n}\n\n\t3.\tPrevent gaps between selectable spans.\nAudit PDF.js text spans for:\n\n\t\342\200\242\tzero-height spans\n\t\342\200\242\tempty spans\n\t\342\200\242\toverlapping spans\n\t\342\200\242\tspacing gaps causing touch loss\n\n\t4.\tAdd invisible selection padding around text lines.\nDo NOT allow selection handles to temporarily leave selectable regions between lines.\n\t5.\tEnsure no overlay intercepts touch near text edges.\nAudit:\n\n\t\342\200\242\tshadows\n\t\342\200\242\tpseudo-elements\n\t\342\200\242\tpage-peek layers\n\t\342\200\242\tgradient overlays\n\t\342\200\242\tspread seam effects\n\t\342\200\242\tdebug overlays\n\nSet:\n\npointer-events: none;\n\non all decorative layers.\n\t6.\tSpecifically test Arabic selection extension.\nEnsure extending selection from RTL words does NOT trigger ancestor/page selection fallback.\n\t7.\tAdd diagnostic logging:\nLog the exact DOM node returned by:\n\ndocument.elementFromPoint(x, y)\n\nduring selection-handle movement near failing areas.\n\nGoal:\nSelection should either:\n\t\342\200\242\tcontinue selecting text\nOR\n\t\342\200\242\tstop cleanly\n\nIt must NEVER select the entire page/container.\n:::"
    items {
      text: ":::writing{variant=\342\200\234chat_message\342\200\235 id=\342\200\23435821\342\200\235}\nInvestigate mobile text selection overflow bug in the PDF reader.\n\nCurrent issue:\nWhen selecting text and dragging selection handles near the end of a word/line, the browser suddenly falls back to selecting the entire page/container instead of continuing precise text selection.\n\nThis mainly happens:\n\t\342\200\242\tnear line edges\n\t\342\200\242\tnear page top\n\t\342\200\242\twhen extending Arabic text selection\n\t\342\200\242\twhen selection leaves valid text spans momentarily\n\nLikely cause:\nThe browser is losing valid selectable text targets and falling back to the nearest selectable ancestor/container.\n\nRequired fixes:\n\t1.\tPrevent ALL parent/container selection fallback.\nApply:\n\n.page,\n.page-wrapper,\n.reader-sheet,\n.spread-page,\n.transform-container {\n  user-select: none !important;\n  -webkit-user-select: none !important;\n}\n\nOnly .textLayer and .textLayer span should remain selectable.\n\t2.\tStrengthen text span hit areas.\nApply:\n\n.textLayer span {\n  display: inline-block;\n  min-height: 1em;\n  padding-top: 1px;\n  padding-bottom: 1px;\n}\n\n\t3.\tPrevent gaps between selectable spans.\nAudit PDF.js text spans for:\n\n\t\342\200\242\tzero-height spans\n\t\342\200\242\tempty spans\n\t\342\200\242\toverlapping spans\n\t\342\200\242\tspacing gaps causing touch loss\n\n\t4.\tAdd invisible selection padding around text lines.\nDo NOT allow selection handles to temporarily leave selectable regions between lines.\n\t5.\tEnsure no overlay intercepts touch near text edges.\nAudit:\n\n\t\342\200\242\tshadows\n\t\342\200\242\tpseudo-elements\n\t\342\200\242\tpage-peek layers\n\t\342\200\242\tgradient overlays\n\t\342\200\242\tspread seam effects\n\t\342\200\242\tdebug overlays\n\nSet:\n\npointer-events: none;\n\non all decorative layers.\n\t6.\tSpecifically test Arabic selection extension.\nEnsure extending selection from RTL words does NOT trigger ancestor/page selection fallback.\n\t7.\tAdd diagnostic logging:\nLog the exact DOM node returned by:\n\ndocument.elementFromPoint(x, y)\n\nduring selection-handle movement near failing areas.\n\nGoal:\nSelection should either:\n\t\342\200\242\tcontinue selecting text\nOR\n\t\342\200\242\tstop cleanly\n\nIt must NEVER select the entire page/container.\n:::"
