    thinking: "**Preventing Parent Selection**\n\nI\'m working to prevent the \"Selection Handle\" from triggering parent selections, which could be problematic. I\'ve considered that dragging a handle over a `user-select: none` element in some browsers might release, which needs to be handled elegantly.\n\n\n**Investigating Overlay Properties**\n\nI\'m now investigating various overlay properties to understand how they might interact with selections. I\'ve found a `selection-overlay-layer` with `pointer-events: none` and confirmed that the bookmarks gradient also has `pointer-events: none` on specific lines in `PDFReader.tsx`. I\'ve also addressed the issue of jumping in Arabic text selection by strengthening spans with `display: inline-block`, `min-height: 1.1em`, `padding-top: 1px`, and `box-sizing: content-box`. I then considered if the padding was going to shift the text (since it\'s `position: absolute`), but the `textLayer` uses a transparent color, so it won\'t affect the visual output.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 2
      nanos: 927077231
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
