  planner_response {
    modified_response: "I\'ve implemented the requested fixes to stabilize text selection and prevent the browser from jumping to select the entire page.\n\n### \360\237\233\240\357\270\217 Fixes Implemented:\n\n*   **Strict Selection Confinement**: I applied `user-select: none` to the entire reader hierarchy (`.pdf-reader-root`, `.reader-sheet`, `.spread-page`, `.transform-container`). This forces the browser to only recognize text within the `.textLayer` spans, effectively disabling the fallback mechanism that selects the whole container.\n*   **Segment Hit-Area Expansion**: \n    *   Optimized text spans with `display: inline-block` and a `min-height: 1.1em`.\n    *   Added **invisible padding** to spans to eliminate gaps between lines and words where selection handles previously \"slipped\" and lost focus.\n    *   Ensured all spans use `box-sizing: content-box` to expand hit targets without breaking PDF.js positioning.\n*   **Decorative Layer Isolation**: Audited all overlays including shadow gradients and spread seams to ensure they have `pointer-events: none`, preventing them from intercepting touch near page edges.\n*   **Diagnostic Logging**: Added logic to track the pointer position during active selection. It will now log a warning to the console identifying the exact DOM node if the selection focus drifts outside of a valid text layer.\n\nThese changes provide a much more stable selection experience, particularly for RTL/Arabic text where precise handle control is critical near line boundaries."
