  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Refining Mobile Text Selection**\n\nI\'ve been focusing on enhancing mobile text selection. Recently, I\'ve implemented \"Selection Bridges,\" adding padding to text spans. This aims to eliminate \"dead zones\" where selection fails. The next step is evaluating the effectiveness of this approach across different mobile browsers and devices, with additional changes being considered.\n\n\n**Addressing Selection Gaps**\n\nI\'ve tackled \"dead zones\" by implementing \"Selection Bridges.\" I\'ve added code to disable custom pan logic (`handlePanStart` and `handlePanMove`) when the OS has an active text selection. Furthermore, I\'ve reinforced `user-select: none` on containers, and refined logging for touch point tracking during selection. Now I\'m checking ReaderSheet, considering transforms like `rotateY` and `perspective` that may affect coordinate accuracy.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 3
      nanos: 213293916
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
