    started_at {
      seconds: 1778938115
      nanos: 290858257
    }
  }
  planner_response {
    modified_response: "I\'ve implemented a comprehensive fix for the mobile text selection issues. The primary cause of \"jumps\" and \"selecting the whole page\" on phones is usually the browser losing track of valid selectable text targets when a touch point or selection handle falls into a \"dead zone\" between lines or words.\n\n### Key Fixes Applied:\n\n1.  **Selection Bridges (CSS)**:\n    *   Added **invisible horizontal and vertical padding** to all text spans (`.textLayer span`). This effectively bridges the gaps between words and lines.\n    *   Even if the finger or selection handle isn\'t perfectly on a glyph, it will still hit the \"selectable area\" of the span, preventing the browser from cancelling the selection or falling back to the parent container.\n    *   Used a combination of `padding` and negative `margin` to ensure hit areas expand without moving the text visually or breaking layout coordinates.\n\n2.  **Gesture Guarding (JS)**:\n    *   Hard-coded a **stop to all custom panning and page-turning gestures** in `PDFReader.tsx` if a text selection range is active (`window.getSelection().type === \'Range\'`).\n    *   This prevents the app from trying to move the page if the browser misidentifies a selection handle drag as a page swipe.\n\n3.  **Parent Selection Fallback Prevention**:\n    *   Applied `user-select: none` and `-webkit-touch-callout: none` to all parent containers (`.reader-sheet`, `.page-view-container`, etc.). This forces the OS to recognize that only the `.textLayer` content is valid for selection, stopping \"Select All\" accidents.\n\n4.  **Diagnostic Logging**:\n    *   Updated the logging to specifically track whenever the pointer leaves a valid text area during an active selection, which will help us pinpoint any remaining \"holes\" if they exist.\n\nThese changes significantly improve the \"stickiness\" of text selection on mobile devices, making it much harder for the browser to lose selection context."
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
steps {
  type: CORTEX_STEP_TYPE_USER_INPUT
  status: CORTEX_STEP_STATUS_DONE
  metadata {
    created_at {
      seconds: 1778938273
      nanos: 630394346
    }
    source: CORTEX_STEP_SOURCE_USER_EXPLICIT
  }
  user_input {
    user_response: "The remaining iOS Safari selection bug occurs when dragging through EMPTY SPACE after a selected word.\n\nObserved behavior:\n- user selects a word\n- finger moves through whitespace at end of line\n- selection suddenly reverses or jumps backward\n- sometimes large page regions become selected\n- once another word is touched, selection corrects itself\n\nThis confirms:\nSafari loses the active selection anchor when the pointer enters non-selectable gaps between fragmented pdf.js spans.\n\n========================\nROOT CAUSE\n========================\n\npdf.js text spans create discontinuous hit regions.\n\nWhitespace after words is not part of a stable selectable row.\n\nSafari selection engine falls through to unrelated spans/paragraphs.\n\n========================\nGOAL\n========================\n\nCreate CONTINUOUS LINE HIT REGIONS.\n\nDragging through whitespace must remain attached to the same text row.\n\n========================\nCRITICAL FIXES\n========================\n\n1. SYNTHETIC LINE WRAPPERS\n========================\n\nGroup text spans into logical line containers.\n\nEach line wrapper should:\n- span full row width\n- slightly overlap vertically with adjacent rows\n- eliminate dead whitespace zones\n\n========================\n2. CONTINUOUS HIT AREA\n========================\n\nWhitespace between words must still belong to the same line hitbox.\n\nDo NOT rely on individual glyph spans for hit-testing continuity.\n\n========================\n3. STABILIZE TEXT GEOMETRY\n========================\n\nRound all:\n- top\n- left\n- width\n- height\n\nAvoid fractional coordinates.\n\nSafari selection becomes unstable on fragmented fractional layouts.\n\n========================\n4. POINTER EVENT ISOLATION\n========================\n\nEnsure ONLY text layer receives selection hit-testing.\n\nSet:\ncanvas layers => pointer-events:none\noverlay layers => pointer-events:none\n\n========================\n5. NO TRANSFORM MUTATION DURING SELECTION\n========================\n\nFreeze:\n- zoom transforms\n- pan transforms\n- tile rerenders\n\nduring active text selection.\n\n========================\n6. DEBUG HIT ZONES\n========================\n\nAdd temporary visualization:\n- line wrapper bounds\n- whitespace hit regions\n- row overlap areas\n\nNeed to verify:\nthere are no dead gaps after words.\n\n========================\nIMPORTANT\n========================\n\nDo NOT attempt more:\n- selection color hacks\n- overlay timing hacks\n- debounce tricks\n\nThe issue is now:\nTEXT HIT-TEST CONTINUITY.\n\n========================\nTARGET\n========================\n\nDragging through empty line space should behave like:\n- Apple Books\n- native iOS text selection\n- Kindle\n\nSelection anchor must remain stable even when finger is between words or beyond last glyph."
    items {
      text: "The remaining iOS Safari selection bug occurs when dragging through EMPTY SPACE after a selected word.\n\nObserved behavior:\n- user selects a word\n- finger moves through whitespace at end of line\n- selection suddenly reverses or jumps backward\n- sometimes large page regions become selected\n- once another word is touched, selection corrects itself\n\nThis confirms:\nSafari loses the active selection anchor when the pointer enters non-selectable gaps between fragmented pdf.js spans.\n\n========================\nROOT CAUSE\n========================\n\npdf.js text spans create discontinuous hit regions.\n\nWhitespace after words is not part of a stable selectable row.\n\nSafari selection engine falls through to unrelated spans/paragraphs.\n\n========================\nGOAL\n========================\n\nCreate CONTINUOUS LINE HIT REGIONS.\n\nDragging through whitespace must remain attached to the same text row.\n\n========================\nCRITICAL FIXES\n========================\n\n1. SYNTHETIC LINE WRAPPERS\n========================\n\nGroup text spans into logical line containers.\n\nEach line wrapper should:\n- span full row width\n- slightly overlap vertically with adjacent rows\n- eliminate dead whitespace zones\n\n========================\n2. CONTINUOUS HIT AREA\n========================\n\nWhitespace between words must still belong to the same line hitbox.\n\nDo NOT rely on individual glyph spans for hit-testing continuity.\n\n========================\n3. STABILIZE TEXT GEOMETRY\n========================\n\nRound all:\n- top\n- left\n- width\n- height\n\nAvoid fractional coordinates.\n\nSafari selection becomes unstable on fragmented fractional layouts.\n\n========================\n4. POINTER EVENT ISOLATION\n========================\n\nEnsure ONLY text layer receives selection hit-testing.\n\nSet:\ncanvas layers => pointer-events:none\noverlay layers => pointer-events:none\n\n========================\n5. NO TRANSFORM MUTATION DURING SELECTION\n========================\n\nFreeze:\n- zoom transforms\n- pan transforms\n- tile rerenders\n\nduring active text selection.\n\n========================\n6. DEBUG HIT ZONES\n========================\n\nAdd temporary visualization:\n- line wrapper bounds\n- whitespace hit regions\n- row overlap areas\n\nNeed to verify:\nthere are no dead gaps after words.\n\n========================\nIMPORTANT\n========================\n\nDo NOT attempt more:\n- selection color hacks\n- overlay timing hacks\n- debounce tricks\n\nThe issue is now:\nTEXT HIT-TEST CONTINUITY.\n\n========================\nTARGET\n========================\n\nDragging through empty line space should behave like:\n- Apple Books\n- native iOS text selection\n- Kindle\n\nSelection anchor must remain stable even when finger is between words or beyond last glyph."
    }
  }
}
