    user_response: "The synthetic line wrappers did NOT fix the issue because they are likely becoming selectable themselves.\n\nCurrent behavior:\n- user selects a word\n- finger moves into whitespace after the word\n- selection reverses or jumps to large page regions\n\nThis strongly suggests Safari is reanchoring selection onto the synthetic hitbox elements instead of the real text spans.\n\n========================\nCRITICAL UNDERSTANDING\n========================\n\nThe line wrappers must NEVER become selectable content.\n\nOnly the actual pdf.js text spans should own text selection.\n\nThe wrappers should assist touch continuity ONLY.\n\n========================\nFIX REQUIRED\n========================\n\nCurrent implementation likely uses:\nuser-select:text\n\non:\n.text-line-hitbox\n\nThis is wrong.\n\nSafari may start selecting the transparent overlay div itself.\n\n========================\nNEW RULES\n========================\n\n1. HITBOXES MUST NOT BE SELECTABLE\n========================\n\nSet:\n.text-line-hitbox {\n  user-select: none;\n  -webkit-user-select: none;\n}\n\nThey are NOT text containers.\n\n========================\n2. REAL TEXT SPANS REMAIN SELECTABLE\n========================\n\nOnly actual pdf.js text spans should use:\nuser-select:text\n\n========================\n3. HITBOXES MUST NOT OVERLAY TEXT\n========================\n\nDo NOT place hitboxes ABOVE spans.\n\nInstead:\n- place behind text layer\nOR\n- integrate as structural row wrappers\n\nNeed touch continuity WITHOUT replacing selection ownership.\n\n========================\n4. POINTER EVENTS\n========================\n\nAvoid:\npointer-events:auto\n\non large transparent overlays.\n\nThis can hijack Safari hit-testing.\n\nIf hitboxes are needed:\n- use minimal geometry\n- avoid full-page transparent layers\n\n========================\n5. DEBUG THIS DIRECTLY\n========================\n\nTemporarily:\n- give hitboxes visible semi-transparent color\n- log event.target during selection drag\n\nNeed to confirm whether Safari is targeting:\n- actual spans\nOR\n- synthetic wrappers\n\n========================\n6. KEEP SELECTION OWNERSHIP SIMPLE\n========================\n\nSelection ownership hierarchy must be:\n\ntext span -> text node\n\nNOT:\noverlay -> wrapper -> transformed container\n\n========================\nIMPORTANT\n========================\n\nDo NOT continue adding:\n- more overlays\n- more selection layers\n- more synthetic selectable elements\n\nThis is now a SELECTION OWNERSHIP problem.\n\n========================\nTARGET\n========================\n\nDragging through whitespace should:\n- preserve original text anchor\n- remain attached to same row\n- never reverse selection\n- never select unrelated page regions"
