g\n\nNeed to confirm whether Safari is targeting:\n- actual spans\nOR\n- synthetic wrappers\n\n========================\n6. KEEP SELECTION OWNERSHIP SIMPLE\n========================\n\nSelection ownership hierarchy must be:\n\ntext span -> text node\n\nNOT:\noverlay -> wrapper -> transformed container\n\n========================\nIMPORTANT\n========================\n\nDo NOT continue adding:\n- more overlays\n- more selection layers\n- more synthetic selectable elements\n\nThis is now a SELECTION OWNERSHIP problem.\n\n========================\nTARGET\n========================\n\nDragging through whitespace should:\n- preserve original text anchor\n- remain attached to same row\n- never reverse selection\n- never select unrelated page regions"
