  }
  user_input {
    user_response: "Yes, this is finally the correct direction.\n\nProceed with the minimal native-selection approach.\n\nBut follow these STRICT constraints.\n\n========================\nCORE PRINCIPLE\n========================\n\nDo NOT create synthetic selectable overlays.\n\nDo NOT replace Safari selection behavior.\n\nKeep native selection ownership attached ONLY to real pdf.js text spans.\n\nWe are fixing:\nSELECTION CONTINUITY,\nnot building a fake selection engine.\n\n========================\nCRITICAL REQUIREMENTS\n========================\n\n1. NO SELECTABLE OVERLAYS\n========================\n\nRemove:\n- synthetic selectable wrappers\n- transparent selectable divs\n- overlay hitbox ownership\n\nOnly actual text spans may be selectable.\n\n========================\n2. PRESERVE NATIVE DOM FLOW\n========================\n\nDo NOT use:\n- margin expansion\n- padding expansion\n- layout-shifting CSS\n\non text spans.\n\nThese can corrupt:\n- glyph positioning\n- selection geometry\n- text alignment\n\n========================\n3. EXPAND HIT REGIONS SAFELY\n========================\n\nIf expanding selectable continuity:\nDO NOT affect layout.\n\nUse non-layout techniques only.\n\nExamples:\n- pseudo-elements\n- transparent outlines\n- internal absolute hit expansion\n- non-layout visual expansion\n\nGoal:\nbridge micro-gaps between fragmented spans\nWITHOUT moving text geometry.\n\n========================\n4. KEEP CANVAS LAYERS NON-INTERACTIVE\n========================\n\nCanvas/tile/render layers MUST remain:\npointer-events:none\n\nOtherwise Safari touch routing becomes unstable.\n\nOnly actual text spans should receive selection interaction.\n\n========================\n5. STABILIZE SPAN GEOMETRY\n========================\n\nNormalize:\n- line-height\n- span height\n- top/left rounding\n\nAvoid fractional pixel instability.\n\nSafari selection becomes unstable with fragmented transformed spans.\n\n========================\n6. NO NEW OVERLAY SYSTEMS\n========================\n\nDo NOT:\n- add more overlay compositors\n- create selection wrappers\n- synthesize selection ownership\n\nThe issue is continuity between native spans.\n\n========================\n7. KEEP TEXT SEMI-REAL\n========================\n\nAvoid:\ncolor: transparent\n\nPrefer:\nrgba(0,0,0,0.01)\n\nSafari selection breaks on fully transparent selectable text.\n\n========================\n8. DEBUGGING\n========================\n\nTemporarily visualize:\n- span bounds\n- line gaps\n- whitespace regions\n\nNeed to confirm:\nthere are no dead hit-test gaps between adjacent spans.\n\n========================\nTARGET\n========================\n\nDragging through:\n- spaces between words\n- end of lines\n- transition to next line\n\nmust remain continuously attached to the same native selection range,\nwithout reversals or page-wide jumps.\n\nBehavior should feel close to:\n- Apple Books\n- Kindle\n- PDF Expert mobile"
    items {
      text: "Yes, this is finally the correct direction.\n\nProceed with the minimal native-selection approach.\n\nBut follow these STRICT constraints.\n\n========================\nCORE PRINCIPLE\n========================\n\nDo NOT create synthetic selectable overlays.\n\nDo NOT replace Safari selection behavior.\n\nKeep native selection ownership attached ONLY to real pdf.js text spans.\n\nWe are fixing:\nSELECTION CONTINUITY,\nnot building a fake selection engine.\n\n========================\nCRITICAL REQUIREMENTS\n========================\n\n1. NO SELECTABLE OVERLAYS\n========================\n\nRemove:\n- synthetic selectable wrappers\n- transparent selectable divs\n- overlay hitbox ownership\n\nOnly actual text spans may be selectable.\n\n========================\n2. PRESERVE NATIVE DOM FLOW\n========================\n\nDo NOT use:\n- margin expansion\n- padding expansion\n- layout-shifting CSS\n\non text spans.\n\nThese can corrupt:\n- glyph positioning\n- selection geometry\n- text alignment\n\n========================\n3. EXPAND HIT REGIONS SAFELY\n========================\n\nIf expanding selectable continuity:\nDO NOT affect layout.\n\nUse non-layout techniques only.\n\nExamples:\n- pseudo-elements\n- transparent outlines\n- internal absolute hit expansion\n- non-layout visual expansion\n\nGoal:\nbridge micro-gaps between fragmented spans\nWITHOUT moving text geometry.\n\n========================\n4. KEEP CANVAS LAYERS NON-INTERACTIVE\n========================\n\nCanvas/tile/render layers MUST remain:\npointer-events:none\n\nOtherwise Safari touch routing becomes unstable.\n\nOnly actual text spans should receive selection interaction.\n\n========================\n5. STABILIZE SPAN GEOMETRY\n========================\n\nNormalize:\n- line-height\n- span height\n- top/left rounding\n\nAvoid fractional pixel instability.\n\nSafari selection becomes unstable with fragmented transformed spans.\n\n========================\n6. NO NEW OVERLAY SYSTEMS\n========================\n\nDo NOT:\n- add more overlay compositors\n- create selection wrappers\n- synthesize selection ownership\n\nThe issue is continuity between native spans.\n\n========================\n7. KEEP TEXT SEMI-REAL\n========================\n\nAvoid:\ncolor: transparent\n\nPrefer:\nrgba(0,0,0,0.01)\n\nSafari selection breaks on fully transparent selectable text.\n\n========================\n8. DEBUGGING\n========================\n\nTemporarily visualize:\n- span bounds\n- line gaps\n- whitespace regions\n\nNeed to confirm:\nthere are no dead hit-test gaps between adjacent spans.\n\n========================\nTARGET\n========================\n\nDragging through:\n- spaces between words\n- end of lines\n- transition to next line\n\nmust remain continuously attached to the same native selection range,\nwithout reversals or page-wide jumps.\n\nBehavior should feel close to:\n- Apple Books\n- Kindle\n- PDF Expert mobile"
    }
  }
}
