  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Addressing Text Selection Frustration**\n\nI\'m currently focused on the frustrating text selection experience within the PDF reader, especially on mobile. My main concern right now revolves around the gesture recognition: when the user\'s touch slips into what the browser perceives as \"empty space\" during a selection attempt. The result is an undesired deselection, which is an extremely irritating user experience.\n\n\n**Refining Gap Bridging**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on gap bridging in the CSS, specifically implementing this safely without causing layout shifts. My plan involves enforcing `user-select: none` on nearly everything, except for the text spans and the text layer. I\'m focusing on ensuring this solution aligns with the native selection ownership guidelines, so I can bridge gaps in a way that respects the user\'s initial intention without any frustrating jumps or unexpected behaviour. I am making sure to clean up any old hacks before implementing new ones.\n\n\n**Analyzing Safari Span Behavior**\n\nI\'m now diving into Safari\'s peculiar handling of gaps between `<span>` elements during text selection. The challenge is clear: bridging these micro-gaps without shifting text geometry, as per the user\'s constraints. I\'ve ruled out margin/padding due to the no-layout shift rule. It seems like using a pseudo-element on each span to cover its right-side gap might be the key. My focus is also on avoiding the common Safari issue with `user-select: none` on parents.\n\n\n**Implementing CSS Refinement**\n\nI\'m now implementing the CSS refactor. First, I cleaned up `index.css`. Next, I focused on modifying the `.textLayer span` styles to use `user-select: text` and made it `inline-block`. I\'m now testing the core fix: Using an `::after` pseudo-element on the span to extend into the whitespace, without shifting the span itself. The crucial part is to avoid new overlay systems or synthetic selectable elements.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 3
      nanos: 809016491
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
